INSERT INTO Articles VALUES("37","1","43 Days Until CruiseFest!","<p><!--StartFragment--></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">CRUISEFEST SWING DANCE CRUISE </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">Sept. 20-27, 2009 </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Only 43 more days until I prop my feel up on a railing overlooking the Pacific Ocean as I cruise off the Mexican Riviera, sipping my drinky-drink and finally able to sit down and relax. If I\'m out at sea then I can\'t go back and do \"one last thing,\" now can I? There\'s something to be said for forced vacation, LOL, so I am counting the days until I can<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>dance with my honey and all my dance friends, the pros, the event organizers, the students and cruise goers, and I love, love, love the thought of dancing and teaching at sea, too cool. I\'m even thinking about upgrading to one of those fancy outside private balcony cabins, how oooh-la-la can you get? Can&rsquo;t you just picture it now??? </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Sign up to through Trish Connery and DanceChatter.Com to join this cruise and get&nbsp;special DanceChatter cruise perks (the DanceChatter (in)FamousCocktail Party + Free 30-Minute Private Lessons), take advantage of&nbsp;dance classes with top pros (Trish Connery &amp; David Walkup, Ben &amp;&nbsp;Melina, Martin Parker, Patti Jobst, Skippy Blair, Kelly Casanova),&nbsp;dance parties and special shore excursions specifically designed for&nbsp;our dance group (including stops in Mazatlan, Cabo San Lucas, and&nbsp;Puerto Vallarta).</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Contact Trish or visit DanceFun&nbsp;website: &nbsp;http://tinyurl.com/db7sf2</span></p>\n<!--EndFragment-->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","1249597048","Aug","2009","Article");
INSERT INTO Articles VALUES("38","21","Salsera Christina Haggerty","<p><!--StartFragment-->\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;;\">SALSERA CHRISTINA HAGGERTY </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Back before I barely dipped my toe in the Salsa pool I had seen&nbsp;the name Christina Haggerty advertised at the Salsa venues but at the time&nbsp;didn&rsquo;t know who she was. I always remembered the name though because&nbsp;it so closely resembled that of Kris Hagerty who used to partner,&nbsp;teach and dance with WCS&rsquo;er Sonny Watson. Remember those days? Tuesday&nbsp;nights at the Crest in Reseda, Sunday classes with Sonny and Kris, the&nbsp;SwingShift dance team?</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Swing dancer Kris dropped out of the dance scene long ago but Salsera&nbsp;Christina Haggerty is very much present and over the SoCal Salsa Scene. She&rsquo;s got agazillion projects going on all at once including Jay Byam&rsquo;s Salsa&nbsp;Extravaganza (Aug 15-17, Palm Springs) not to mention Salsa and Cha Cha classes&nbsp;all over town. Plus, she&rsquo;s got fierce Salsa leading skills,&nbsp;something you know I totally respect. Check out her website for a list&nbsp;of classes, dances, workshops and more: www.mikechristina.com&nbsp;</span></p>\n<!--EndFragment--></p>","1249597315","Aug","2009","Article");
INSERT INTO Articles VALUES("39","22","Francisco Aguabella 2Nite @ Autry","<p><!--StartFragment--></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">SIZZLIN&rsquo; SUMMER SALSA @ AUTRY CENTER </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">Francisco Aquabella at the Autry Thursday, August 6th </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">6:00-9:00 pm; Beginning Salsa Lesson with Trish @ 7:30 pm </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">Autry National Center, 4700 Western Heritage Drive, Los Angeles, 90027 </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \">At Griffith Park, across from Los Angeles Zoo, Plenty of free, safe&nbsp;parking, Autrynationalcenter.org&nbsp;</span></p>\n<!--EndFragment-->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","1249597395","Aug","2009","Article");
INSERT INTO Articles VALUES("40","3","New 6-Week Series/Burbank: WCS + C2S","<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">DanceChatter.Com Presents <br />West Coast Swing + Country 2-Step <br />Every Tuesday with Trish Connery </span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><br />New 6-Week Series Starts Tuesday, August 18th </span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><br />7:30 pm - Beginning West Coast Swing (Level 1) <br />You\'ve seen it on \"So You Think You Can Dance\" and \"Dancing With The <br />Stars\", now learn this fun and creative form of swing dancing for yourself, <br />from the ground up! No experience needed, no partner required. <br />30-minute class, $5 per single class or $30 for the 6-week series <br />Moose Lodge Members receive $5 off the series </span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><br />8:00 pm - Beyond Basics West Coast Swing (Level 2) <br />Already know your basics? This class is the next step. <br />55 minute class, $10 per single class, $48 for the 6-week series <br />$43 if registered in advance via Paypal (send fee to trish@dancechatter.com), Moose Lodge Members receive $5 off the series.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"> <br />9:00 pm - Beginning &amp; Beyond Country 2-Step (Levels 1 &amp; 2) <br />Country 2-Step is easy, fast and Yee-Haw! Fun is a must, hats are <br />optional! 55 minute class, $10 per single class, $48 for the 6-week series <br />$43 if registered in advance via Paypal (send fee to trish@dancechatter.com), Moose Lodge Members receive $5 off the series.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"> <br />Sign up for Beyond Basics West Coast Swing -AND- Country 2-Step and <br />SAVE! Take BOTH 6-week series for only $80 if registered in advance (Paypal fee to trish@dancechatter.com).</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><br />Burbank Moose Lodge <br />1901 W. Burbank Blvd. <br />(off of Buena Vista) <br />Burbank, 91505 <br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Trish Connery &amp; DanceChatter.Com <br />323-228-3532; trish@dancechatter.com; www.dancechatter.com </span></span></p>","1250554357","Aug","2009","Article");
INSERT INTO Articles VALUES("41","1","DanceChatter Part 1: Missing In Action","<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <o:DocumentProperties> <o:Template>Normal.dotm</o:Template> <o:Revision>0</o:Revision> <o:TotalTime>0</o:TotalTime> <o:Pages>1</o:Pages> <o:Words>400</o:Words> <o:Characters>2285</o:Characters> <o:Company>Hohman Maybank Lieb</o:Company> <o:Lines>19</o:Lines> <o:Paragraphs>4</o:Paragraphs> <o:CharactersWithSpaces>2806</o:CharactersWithSpaces> <o:Version>12.0</o:Version> </o:DocumentProperties> <o:OfficeDocumentSettings> <o:AllowPNG /> </o:OfficeDocumentSettings> </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves>false</w:TrackMoves> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:DrawingGridHorizontalSpacing>18 pt</w:DrawingGridHorizontalSpacing> <w:DrawingGridVerticalSpacing>18 pt</w:DrawingGridVerticalSpacing> <w:DisplayHorizontalDrawingGridEvery>0</w:DisplayHorizontalDrawingGridEvery> <w:DisplayVerticalDrawingGridEvery>0</w:DisplayVerticalDrawingGridEvery> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables /> <w:DontGrowAutofit /> <w:DontAutofitConstrainedTables /> <w:DontVertAlignInTxbx /> </w:Compatibility> </w:WordDocument> </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"276\"> </w:LatentStyles> </xml><![endif]--> <!--  /* Font Definitions */ @font-face 	{font-family:Geneva; 	panose-1:2 11 5 3 3 4 4 4 2 4; 	mso-font-charset:0; 	mso-generic-font-family:auto; 	mso-font-pitch:variable; 	mso-font-signature:3 0 0 0 1 0;} @font-face 	{font-family:\"American Typewriter\"; 	panose-1:2 9 6 4 2 0 4 2 3 4; 	mso-font-charset:0; 	mso-generic-font-family:auto; 	mso-font-pitch:variable; 	mso-font-signature:3 0 0 0 1 0;}  /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal 	{mso-style-parent:\"\"; 	margin:0in; 	margin-bottom:.0001pt; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:12.0pt; 	font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";} @page Section1 	{size:8.5in 11.0in; 	margin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in; 	mso-header-margin:.5in; 	mso-footer-margin:.5in; 	mso-paper-source:0;} div.Section1 	{page:Section1;} --> <!--[if gte mso 10]> <mce:style><!   /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable 	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; 	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; 	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; 	mso-style-noshow:yes; 	mso-style-parent:\"\"; 	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; 	mso-para-margin:0in; 	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:12.0pt; 	font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-ascii-font-family:Cambria; 	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast; 	mso-hansi-font-family:Cambria; 	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;} --> <!--[endif]--> <!--StartFragment--><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">DanceChatter Newsletter 8-24-09: Part 1</span><br /></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\">DanceChatter Newsletter; Missing in Action</span></span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I know, I know, it&rsquo;s been a couple of weeks since I&rsquo;ve sent out an e-mail, I hope y&rsquo;all forgive me. My schedule has been pretty packed to say the least. As you may know I started Salsa classes at the Burbank Moose Lodge (BML) on Wednesday nights, and the Tuesday night West Coast Swing and Country 2-Step classes, also at the BML, continue to flourish (good word, flourish), and of course WCS &amp; Ballroom Sundays at the Hacienda. Jay Byam&rsquo;s Summer Dance Camp in Palm Springs at the beginning of August was a hoot, we had over 20 people packed into our hotel room on Friday night of the event for our traditional DanceChatter.Com Cocktail Party. I&rsquo;m so glad that so many of &ldquo;my&rdquo; people came with us and had such a good time. For some it was their first event and they thoroughly enjoyed it as did everyone. </span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Over the years I&rsquo;ve noticed that my focus at conventions has changed somewhat. It used to be that I was the stay-up-late-and-dance &lsquo;til all hours girl. Now it seems that between work and teaching and life, I&rsquo;m so busy all the time that when I make it out to a convention I lean more toward rest and relaxation or should I say collapse and coma, LOL (once I get my teaching and judging obligations out of the way, that is). I know you wouldn&rsquo;t think it but sometimes conventions are the only quiet time I seem to have &ndash; kind of like going to the movies to take a nap (which I&rsquo;ve also done, LOL). Is that a good thing? Or just plain sad?? At any rate, whether we were resting or dancing or just hanging out together, Summer Dance Camp was a lot of fun, as always. And, just throwing this out there, speaking of Jay Byam&rsquo;s events, folks are already asking to be part of the DanceChatter Group for New Year&rsquo;s Dance Camp, my tables WILL sell out (they always do), so keep that in mind, NYDC is only four months away!</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In other news, my mother, Mary Kathryn, was out for a brief visit a few weeks ago, some of you in the Tuesday and Wednesday night classes at the BML got a chance to meet her. She and her husband Lowell will be joining David and I our CruiseFest Swing Dance Cruise coming up in September (only 28 days away!), can&rsquo;t wait for that. I had a couple of great weekends down in San Diego but my weekends tend to be really short as I always head back to LA on Sunday in order to teach. Speaking of teaching on Sunday, I want to mention the DanceChatter Performance Class which practices on Sundays. I want to give them a shout-out (David, Elaine, Jon, Diana, Scott, Rochelle, Eric, Susan, Dennis, Denise, Brian, Alice) for being such good troopers. We are putting the final touches on our routine and will be putting it out there on the floor in the not-too-distant future; I am so very proud of them.</span></span></p>\n<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <o:DocumentProperties> <o:Template>Normal.dotm</o:Template> <o:Revision>0</o:Revision> <o:TotalTime>0</o:TotalTime> <o:Pages>1</o:Pages> <o:Words>182</o:Words> <o:Characters>1038</o:Characters> <o:Company>Hohman Maybank Lieb</o:Company> <o:Lines>8</o:Lines> <o:Paragraphs>2</o:Paragraphs> <o:CharactersWithSpaces>1274</o:CharactersWithSpaces> <o:Version>12.0</o:Version> </o:DocumentProperties> <o:OfficeDocumentSettings> <o:AllowPNG /> </o:OfficeDocumentSettings> </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves>false</w:TrackMoves> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:DrawingGridHorizontalSpacing>18 pt</w:DrawingGridHorizontalSpacing> <w:DrawingGridVerticalSpacing>18 pt</w:DrawingGridVerticalSpacing> <w:DisplayHorizontalDrawingGridEvery>0</w:DisplayHorizontalDrawingGridEvery> <w:DisplayVerticalDrawingGridEvery>0</w:DisplayVerticalDrawingGridEvery> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables /> <w:DontGrowAutofit /> <w:DontAutofitConstrainedTables /> <w:DontVertAlignInTxbx /> </w:Compatibility> </w:WordDocument> </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"276\"> </w:LatentStyles> </xml><![endif]--> <!--  /* Font Definitions */ @font-face 	{font-family:Calibri; 	panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; 	mso-font-charset:0; 	mso-generic-font-family:auto; 	mso-font-pitch:variable; 	mso-font-signature:3 0 0 0 1 0;} @font-face 	{font-family:\"Academy Engraved LET\"; 	panose-1:2 0 5 0 0 0 0 0 0 0; 	mso-font-charset:0; 	mso-generic-font-family:auto; 	mso-font-pitch:variable; 	mso-font-signature:3 0 0 0 1 0;}  /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal 	{mso-style-parent:\"\"; 	margin:0in; 	margin-bottom:.0001pt; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:12.0pt; 	font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";} @page Section1 	{size:8.5in 11.0in; 	margin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in; 	mso-header-margin:.5in; 	mso-footer-margin:.5in; 	mso-paper-source:0;} div.Section1 	{page:Section1;} --> <!--[if gte mso 10]> <mce:style><!   /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable 	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; 	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; 	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; 	mso-style-noshow:yes; 	mso-style-parent:\"\"; 	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; 	mso-para-margin:0in; 	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:12.0pt; 	font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-ascii-font-family:Cambria; 	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast; 	mso-hansi-font-family:Cambria; 	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;} --> <!--[endif]--> <!--StartFragment--></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\"><span style=\"color: black;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This past Friday night David and I headed out to do some ballroom dancing at the <strong>Glendale Moose Lodge</strong>. <strong>Janet E</strong> who attends Tuesday night classes at the BML told me about their regular Friday night dances and we decided to check it out. Beautiful facility, gorgeous floor very nice people and a wide variety of DJ music &ndash; Waltz&rsquo;s, Cha&rsquo;s, Tango&rsquo;s, Foxtrot, even a few Hustles, WCS&rsquo;s and a Country 2-Step thrown in. We were a little too tired to make a late night of it, but it was a perfect blend of dancing and socializing. Thanks, Janet, for passing on the info and for saving us seats, and thanks to the GML and dancers for such a good time!</span></span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\"><span style=\"color: black;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Saturday we shirked the dance practice we should have in order to run errands. While on the computer that day I posted something about fixing our Saturday morning coffee on Facebook. The power of social networking sites still takes me by surprise sometimes, &lsquo;cause later that same night when we hit <strong>Montana&rsquo;s</strong> in <strong>San Dimas</strong> for some hot Country 2-Step, at least five people came up to me and said &ldquo;Hey, how was that coffee?&rdquo; LOL. Thanks to the awesome dancers who gave me such awesome 2-Steps (David [of course], Ari, Alan C, Woody W, Dean S, Tom H, Chuck), you guys were great!</span></span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: \"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\">Happy Birthday, Steve F!</span></span></span></em></strong></p>\n<!--EndFragment-->\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: book antiqua,palatino;\">Stay tuned for Part 2 of DanceChatter 8-24-09!</span></span><br /></span></p>","1251221628","Aug","2009","Article");
