INSERT INTO Articles VALUES("51","23","7th Tuesday Dance: Success","<p><!--StartFragment--></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10.0pt; mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span><span style=\"font-family: \'lucida grande\', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #333333; line-height: 14px;\">DanceChatter.Com\'s 7th Tuesday Dance / Tuesday, February 16, 2010<br /><br />Wrap-Up: The Day After<br /><br />I want to thank everyone who came out for the very first 7th Tuesday Dance at the Burbank Moose Lodge last night, Tuesday, February 16th. We had a great time!<br /><br />We started out the night with a Beginning West Coast Swing Workshop which was free to \"true newbies,\" ie, those who had never taken a WCS class before. The workshop was filled with newcomers and most of those folks took the plunge and signed up for the Beginning WCS 6-week series that starts next week, February 23rd. We are converting... uh, I mean, introducing new people to West Coast Swing, that\'s what it\'s all about!!<br /><br />The Intermediate West Coast Swing Workshop was really fun, too. We had a lot of familiar faces and existing DanceChatter students, but also new-to-me dancers in that group, as well (many of who signed up for the Beyond Basics WCS 6-week series that starts on February 23rd). We had a full floor, a fun and challenging pattern and by the end of the workshop everyone was all warmed up for social dancing. A particular highlight for me was seeing all those dancers actually using the class material they just learned out there on the social dance floor with success - way to go!<br /><br />DJDK David Koppelman played the best WCS, Hustle, Country 2-Step, Nightclub and Cha Cha music you could possibly hope for, and kept right on playing until there were no more dancers on the floor. His ability to mix the song and dance styles and read the crowd to keep the energy going, keeping everyone happy, is truly a gift.&nbsp;<br /><br />Everyone enjoyed the refreshments - we offered a healthy mix of veggies and fruit, and for a touch of decadence, cookies and those delicious \"brownie bites\".... Mmmmm! Next time though, you all have to promise me that you\'ll eat ALL the brownies before you leave - it\'s dangerous for me to take them home!<br /><br />The Best Dancer Award goes to Chester who&rsquo;s been a DanceChatter student for almost a year. Before the dance I gave Chester, who doesn&rsquo;t get out dancing very much, a mission: \"While at the dance you need to ask 5 women you don\'t know to dance (in addition to the women you already know)\" This was a real challenge for Chester but by golly if he didn\'t do it, I could not be more proud of him, way to go Chester!<br /><br />Special thanks to my volunteers who helped me set up, organize put out the food, work the registration desk and break it all down at the end: Janet, Alice, Gordon, Steve, Dennis, Denise, and Chip. I could not have done it without you. However, I have to give a little extra special shout-out to Alice for her mad skills in working the room - ie, talking to all those new folks, making sure everyone was comfortable and having a good time, and most importantly, getting out there and dancing with everyone!&nbsp;<br /><br />Also, special thanks to dance promoter Rhonda Diamond for not only sharing the dance info with her extensive e-mail list but who also made a cameo at the dance as well! Thank you Rhonda, it was a pleasure to have you and Paul in the house! And, folks - make sure you attend Rhonda and DJDK David Koppelman\'s 4th Saturday dance in Lomita on February 27th, it will be a blast! (www.diamondswing.com).&nbsp;<br /><br />I\'d also like to thank James Woo from Dance Buddies and USA Dance for his support in publicizing the dance, for taking the time to come and hang out with us. James, we had a wild WCS, it was fun, thank you for joining us!<br /><br />Thanks also to my Hustle partner in crime, Michele Adams, who although not able to attend (she\'s waaaaaayy down in Orange County), took the time to support the dance via her e-mail list. Quick aside, Michele and I have a Double Diva Hustle Workshop coming up on Saturday, March 6th at the Golden Sails Hotel in Long Beach (www.dancechatter.com). And, did you know? Michele\'s and my Double Diva Hustle Team will be making its debut performance at the upcoming Los Angeles Premiere Dance Classic (April 9-11th, www.lapdclassic.com).&nbsp;<br /><br />And, although I know he usually doesn\'t like me to acknowledge him, I must also say thank you to Bailey, the administrator at the Burbank Moose Lodge. He always makes it so easy for me to teach and work there, making sure the lights are right, the temperature is correct, the sound is working, etc. His attention to detail really makes a difference. Also thanks to Bailey, the dance floor is FANTASTIC (as was commented on by many people).&nbsp;<br /><br />As for me, I had a blast teaching both workshops last night (give me a mic and I\'m happy, LOL), I loved meeting all those new people and seeing so many familiar faces as well, and I did my best to dance with as many of you as possible (I haven\'t lead so much in one night in a while!).&nbsp;<br /><br />See you all next week, Tuesday, February 23rd when we resume the regular Tuesday night classes (7:00 pm Beginning WCS, 8:00 pm Beyond Basics WCS, 9:00 pm Beginning Nightclub) with a new 6-week series, and mark down Tuesday, April 6th as the date for our next 7th Tuesday Dance Party!<br /><br />DanceChatter Out!<br /><br />t<br />---<br />Upcoming DanceChatter Events<br /><br />Sunday, February 21st<br />WCS Critique Session with Trish Connery &amp; David Walkup<br />1:00-3:00 pm<br />Double H Club/Hacienda<br />Advance registration suggestion<br />www.dancechatter.com<br /><br />Tuesday, February 23rd<br />New 6-Week Series at Burbank Moose Lodge<br />7:00 pm-Beg WCS<br />8:00 pm - Beyond Basics WCS<br />9:00 pm - Beg Nightclub<br />$10 per single class<br />$42 per person for 1 6-week series for Moose Lodge members IN ADVANCE<br />$48 per person for 1 6-week series IN ADVANCE<br />$54 person for 1 6-week series at the door<br />Burbank Moose Lodge, 1901 W. Burbank Blvd., Burbank, 91505<br />www.dancechatter.com<br /><br />Saturday, March 6th<br />Double Diva Hustle Workshops<br />Michele Adams &amp; Trish Connery<br />11:00 am-4:00 pm<br />Golden Sails Hotel, Long Beach<br />www.dancechatter.com; www.countrydancesport.com<br /><br />April 9-11th<br />Los Angeles Premiere Dance Classic<br />Marriott/LAX<br />www.lapdclassic.com<br /><br />September 26-October 3, 2010<br />CruiseFest SwingDance Cruise<br />7 Days/Night of Dancing in the Caribbean<br />Trish Connery &amp; David Walkup, Ben Morris &amp; Melina Ramirez, Martin Parker, Patti Jobst, Kelly Casanova, Michael Kielbasa, Samantha Buckwalter, Skippy Blair<br /><a style=\"cursor: pointer; color: #3b5998; text-decoration: none;\" onmousedown=\"UntrustedLink.bootstrap($(this), \" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.dancefun.com/westcoastswing/100926_WesternCaribbean/cruise1_main/main_page.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span>http://www.dancefun.com/we</span><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: block; float: left; margin-left: -10px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</span><span>stcoastswing/100926_Wester</span><span class=\"word_break\" style=\"display: block; float: left; margin-left: -10px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</span><span>nCaribbean/cruise1_main/ma</span>in_page.html</a><br />SIGN UP UNDER TRISH &amp; DAVID</span></span></span></p>\n<!--EndFragment-->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","1266436193","Feb","2010","Article");
